=== fix-case-sensitivity.log: domain-review-precheck.ps1 case-insensitive
    comparison sweep and fix (gate-cycle finding, security-spec B2
    weakened-port defect class, sibling of T-004/#174's 12-site fix in
    2a7eef5) ===

--- 0. Sweep methodology ---

grep -n -- '-match|-notmatch|-replace|-eq |-ne |-contains|-notcontains|
-like|-notlike|switch' plugins/sdd-domain/scripts/domain-review-precheck.ps1

Every hit was cross-checked against domain-review-precheck.sh's actual
bash/jq case-sensitivity semantics (bash `[[ =~ ]]`/`==` and jq `==`/test()
are always case-sensitive; no nocasematch anywhere in the .sh original).

--- 1. Sweep result list (all -match/-notmatch/-replace/-eq/-ne sites) ---

| Line (pre-fix) | Code | Verdict | Reason |
|---|---|---|---|
| 17 | `[switch]$Reset` | not applicable | grep false-positive (param declaration keyword, not a comparison) |
| 43 | `$null -eq $item` | SAFE | null comparison, no string/case concern |
| 59 | `$Attempt -notmatch '^[1-9][0-9]*$'` | SAFE | digit-only pattern, no letters |
| 60 | `$Round -notmatch '^[1-9][0-9]*$'` | SAFE | digit-only pattern, no letters |
| 66 | `$EditSummary -replace '\s', ''` | SAFE | whitespace-only pattern, no letters |
| 69 | `$roundInt -eq 1` | SAFE | integer comparison |
| 71 | `$attemptInt -eq 1` | SAFE | integer comparison |
| 136 | `... -replace '\s', ''` | SAFE | whitespace-only pattern, no letters |
| **137** | `$status -notmatch '^(Pending\|Reviewed\|Approved)$'` | **FIXED** | letters present; .sh `[[ =~ ]]` is case-sensitive (domain-review-precheck.sh:96) -> **`-cnotmatch`** |
| 178 | `$propNames.Count -eq 2` | SAFE | integer comparison |
| **255** | `$_.Name -match '^round-[1-3]$'` | **FIXED** | letters present; .sh `find -name 'round-*'` + case-sensitive sed extraction -> **`-cmatch`** |
| **256** | `$_.Name -replace '^round-', ''` | **HARDENED** | letters present; provably safe post-fix (only ever receives names that already passed the now-case-sensitive line-255 filter), but converted to **`-creplace`** for defense-in-depth / consistency, removing any ambiguity for a future refactor |

Additional broad sweeps confirming no other candidates:
- `grep -n -- '-eq\|-ne\|-ceq\|-cne\|-ieq\|-ine'` -- only the 4 numeric/null
  sites above; every raw string-identity comparison in this file already
  routes through the file's own `Test-OrdinalEqual` helper (ordinal,
