Conclusion: exactly 2 genuine case-sensitivity weakenings (lines 137, 255,
matching the host's diagnosis) plus 1 additional defensive hardening (line
256, not a live divergence but converted for consistency). All other
`-match`/`-notmatch`/`-replace`/`-eq`/`-ne` sites are safe by construction
(digit-only or whitespace-only patterns, or numeric/null comparisons).

